column2: An aqueduct is a channel that carries water from one place to another. It is usually used to supply water to settlements and farms.
A large gold mine that produces a great deal of wealth.
A large silver mine that produces a great deal of wealth.
A large copper mine that produces a great deal of wealth.
The Roman Frontier Line was constructed in the 6th century to safeguard the borders of the empire against its powerful foes.
A multipurpose and centrally located open area surrounded by public buildings that serves as a public gathering place.
There is a large warrior garrison in the castle providing support for the standing army.
A Castrum Stativum with permanent barracks and fortifications beyond that of a normal fort.

Gallus' Wall is a fortification north of Hadrian's Wall. It is not a single fort but a series of them stretching from coast to coast aided by many small milecastles of varying size and strength. Its primary purpose is to delay the march of Pictish invaders towards Hadrian's Wall.
Ballistae have been added to the fortifications of this fort.
The frontiers of this province are regularly patrolled.
There is a small settlement under the protection of the fort.
In addition to the fort's garrison there is a legionary base used in peacetime to house soldiers.
Additional barracks have been constructed here.
This county possesses a mighty palace that concentrates a lot of wealth and power here, making this castle the most powerful in the entire region.
This county possesses a mighty harbour that concentrates a lot of wealth and power here, making this castle the most powerful in the entire region.
This room symbolises the Imperial power that the Emperor of the Cyrodiilic Empire possesses. Many troops are stationed here to protect the Emperor and his Empire.

After a long process, this castle was fortified with a water-filled moat. It provides a formidable defence to the castle, while also allowing its owner to tax the peasants that want to enter the castle.
After constructions that took years, this castles moat looks more like a river than a simple ditch. It provides an impermeable defence to the castle and the bridge tolls are massive.
Here the ragtag of the castle assembles. They are skilled at riding and raiding and can prove a boon in battle and sieges. But they're also a disturbance to the local people.
